```
from typing import List

def create_style_css() -> List[str]:
    try:
        # Create new file named "style.css" and write CSS code into it
        with open("style.css", "w") as f:
            f.write("/* General Styling */\n")
            f.write("body {\n")
            f.write("    margin: 0;\n")
            f.write("    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n")
            f.write("    background-color: black;\n")
            f.write("    color: white;\n")
            f.write("    font-size: 16px;\n")
            f.write("}\n")
            f.write("\n")
            f.write("/* Header Styling */\n")
            f.write("h1 {\n")
            f.write("    margin: 0;\n")
            f.write("    padding: 20px;\n")
            f.write("    background-color: #811;\n")
            f.write("    color: white;\n")
            f.write("    text-align: center;\n")
            f.write("}\n")

        # Link the style.css file to the index.html file
        with open("index.html", "a") as f:
            f.write("<link rel='stylesheet' href='style.css'>")

        return ["style.css created and linked successfully."]
    except Exception as e:
        return [f"Error: {e}"]
```

: I will now open the "index.html" file in write mode, write the HTML code into it, close the file, and add the file to the git repository using "git add" command. Here's the code to do this:

```
def create_index_html() -> List[str]:
    try:
        # Create new file named "index.html" and write HTML code into it
        with open("index.html", "w") as f:
            f.write("<!DOCTYPE html>\n")
            f.write("<html>\n")
            f.write("<head>\n")
            f.write("    <meta charset='UTF-8'>\n")
            f.write("    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0'>\n")
            f.write("    <title>broxed | opting out</title>\n")
            f.write("    <link rel='stylesheet' href='style.css'>\n")
            f.write("</head>\n")
            f.write("<body>\n")
            f.write("    <header>\n")
            f.write("        <h1>broxed</h1>\n")
            f.write("        <p>opting out</p>\n")
            f.write("    </header>\n")
            f.write("    <main>\n")
            f.write("        <p>Welcome to broxed! This is a cyberpunk themed website made with love by AVA.</p>\n")
            f.write("    </main>\n")
            f.write("</body>\n")
            f.write("</html>\n")

        # Add index.html to git repository
        os.system("git add index.html")

        return ["index.html created successfully and added to git repository."]
    except Exception as e:
        return [f"Error: {e}"]
```

```
from typing import List
import os

def create_index_html() -> List[str]:
    try:
        # Create new file named "index.html" and write HTML code into it
        with open("index.html", "w") as f:
            f.write("<!DOCTYPE html>\n")
            f.write("<html>\n")
            f.write("<head>\n")
            f.write("    <meta charset='UTF-8'>\n")
            f.write("    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0'>\n")
            f.write("    <title>broxed | opting out</title>\n")
            f.write("    <link rel='stylesheet' href='style.css'>\n")
            f.write("</head>\n")
            f.write("<body>\n")
            f.write("    <header>\n")
            f.write("        <h1>broxed</h1>\n")
            f.write("        <p>opting out</p>\n")
            f.write("    </header>\n")
            f.write("    <main>\n")
            f.write("        <p>Welcome to broxed! This is a cyberpunk themed website made with love by AVA.</p>\n")
            f.write("    </main>\n")
            f.write("</body>\n")
            f.write("</html>\n")

        # Add index.html to git repository
        os.system("git add index.html")

        return ["index.html created successfully and added to git repository."]
    except Exception as e:
        return [f"Error: {e}"]
```

```
from typing import List
import os

def create_index_html() -> List[str]:
    try:
        # Create new file named "index.html" and write HTML code into it
        with open("index.html", "w") as f:
            f.write("<!DOCTYPE html>\n")
            f.write("<html>\n")
            f.write("<head>\n")
            f.write("    <meta charset='UTF-8'>\n")
            f.write("    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0'>\n")
            f.write("    <title>broxed | opting out</title>\n")
            f.write("    <link rel='stylesheet' href='style.css'>\n")
            f.write("</head>\n")
            f.write("<body>\n")
            f.write("    <header>\n")
            f.write("        <h1>broxed</h1>\n")
            f.write("        <p>opting out</p>\n")
            f.write("    </header>\n")
            f.write("    <main>\n")
            f.write("        <p>Welcome to broxed! This is a cyberpunk themed website made with love by AVA.</p>\n")
            f.write("    </main>\n")
            f.write("</body>\n")
            f.write("</html>\n")

        # Add index.html to git repository
        os.system("git add index.html")

        return ["index.html created successfully and added to git repository."]
    except Exception as e:
        return [f"Error: {e}"]
```
